WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:04.000
Oxford Bookworms Library, starter.

00:05.000 --> 00:09.000
The Mystery of Manor Hall, by Jane Kamak.

00:09.000 --> 00:12.000
Read by David Thorpe.

00:12.000 --> 00:18.000
Published and copyright, Oxford University Press 2013.

00:30.000 --> 00:47.000
The Mystery of Manor Hall.

00:48.000 --> 00:53.000
We don't want to stay with Uncle Henry Mum.

00:53.000 --> 00:57.000
The boy with dark hair and blue eyes

00:57.000 --> 01:02.000
takes his mobile phone out of his pocket.

01:02.000 --> 01:08.000
Grandma says he doesn't like teenagers.

01:08.000 --> 01:11.000
His mother shakes her head

01:11.000 --> 01:15.000
and Tom looks out the window again.

01:15.000 --> 01:18.000
The car goes left.

01:18.000 --> 01:21.000
The sign on the gate says,

01:21.000 --> 01:24.000
Manor Hall.

01:24.000 --> 01:28.000
Manor Hall says the beautiful girl

01:28.000 --> 01:31.000
sitting next to her brother Tom.

01:31.000 --> 01:36.000
Does Uncle Henry live here?

01:36.000 --> 01:41.000
Her mother hears what Millie says.

01:41.000 --> 01:48.000
Henry is strange, but he's nice too.

01:48.000 --> 01:52.000
Can't we come to the new house with you, Mum?

01:52.000 --> 01:56.000
We can help, Millie asks.

01:56.000 --> 02:00.000
No, Millie, says her mum.

02:00.000 --> 02:06.000
There aren't any beds in the new house.

02:06.000 --> 02:09.000
The car stops.

02:09.000 --> 02:13.000
Here we are, says Mum.

02:13.000 --> 02:17.000
The house is very old and dark.

02:17.000 --> 02:21.000
There are lots of small windows.

02:21.000 --> 02:25.000
Millie is afraid.

02:25.000 --> 02:28.000
A man opens the door.

02:28.000 --> 02:35.000
He is old and he has got white hair and big eyebrows.

02:35.000 --> 02:41.000
He looks at Tom and Millie with his grey eyes.

02:41.000 --> 02:46.000
You're late, he says.

02:46.000 --> 02:48.000
Come in.

02:48.000 --> 02:51.000
Sorry, says Tom.

02:51.000 --> 02:54.000
I'm Tom.

02:54.000 --> 02:56.000
How do you do?

02:56.000 --> 03:00.000
The old man looks angry.

03:00.000 --> 03:04.000
And I'm Millie, says Millie.

03:04.000 --> 03:08.000
Your house is very big.

03:08.000 --> 03:13.000
It is, says Uncle Henry.

03:13.000 --> 03:23.000
You can explore, but there is one room where you can't go.

03:23.000 --> 03:33.000
They walk along a corridor and see a sitting room where there are beautiful sofas and pictures on the walls.

03:33.000 --> 03:37.000
Then they come to a door.

03:37.000 --> 03:44.000
This is the music room, says Uncle Henry.

03:44.000 --> 03:47.000
There is a sign on the door.

03:47.000 --> 03:52.000
It says, do not enter.

03:52.000 --> 03:57.000
Why can't we go in there, asks Millie?

03:57.000 --> 04:02.000
I can play the piano and I love music.

04:02.000 --> 04:06.000
Uncle Henry shakes his head.

04:06.000 --> 04:15.000
I can't tell you, but never open this door.

04:15.000 --> 04:19.000
What a strange man.

04:19.000 --> 04:23.000
Tom says when they are in their bedroom.

04:23.000 --> 04:27.000
Why can't we go into the music room?

04:27.000 --> 04:30.000
But Millie isn't listening.

04:30.000 --> 04:35.000
Let's explore, she says.

04:35.000 --> 04:41.000
Tom and Millie walk up and down and open doors.

04:41.000 --> 04:45.000
Then they come to the music room.

04:45.000 --> 04:51.000
Tom is about to open the door when Uncle Henry sees them.

04:51.000 --> 04:57.000
Get away from there, shouts Uncle Henry.

04:57.000 --> 05:07.000
Later, when they are having dinner in the dining room, Uncle Henry is very quiet.

05:07.000 --> 05:10.000
Are you angry with us?

05:10.000 --> 05:12.000
asks Millie.

05:12.000 --> 05:15.000
Uncle Henry doesn't answer.

05:15.000 --> 05:18.000
He shakes his head.

05:18.000 --> 05:25.000
Then he says, there's a full moon tonight.

05:25.000 --> 05:29.000
He gets up and looks out the window.

05:29.000 --> 05:34.000
Lock your bedroom door, he says.

05:34.000 --> 05:38.000
And don't open it.

05:38.000 --> 05:41.000
I don't understand.

05:41.000 --> 05:44.000
Millie says to Tom.

05:44.000 --> 05:48.000
Why does Uncle Henry look at the moon?

05:48.000 --> 05:52.000
Why can't we go into the music room?

05:52.000 --> 05:55.000
It's a mystery.

05:55.000 --> 06:00.000
Tom isn't listening, he's reading a book.

06:00.000 --> 06:05.000
I want to explore, Tom says suddenly.

06:05.000 --> 06:10.000
We can't, says Millie.

06:10.000 --> 06:14.000
It's midnight and Millie wakes up.

06:14.000 --> 06:20.000
It's very dark in the bedroom and she can hear a noise.

06:20.000 --> 06:25.000
She gets out of bed and goes to her brother's bed.

06:25.000 --> 06:27.000
Tom?

06:27.000 --> 06:32.000
Tom, she says, and shakes his arm.

06:32.000 --> 06:35.000
Tom opens his eyes.

06:35.000 --> 06:39.000
Millie, it's late.

06:39.000 --> 06:43.000
Go back to bed.

06:43.000 --> 06:46.000
He closes his eyes again.

06:47.000 --> 06:51.000
Now, Tom, get up.

06:51.000 --> 06:55.000
There's a strange noise.

06:55.000 --> 06:59.000
Tom goes to the door and listens.

06:59.000 --> 07:03.000
You're right, he says to Millie.

07:03.000 --> 07:09.000
I can hear someone singing.

07:09.000 --> 07:12.000
Can Uncle Henry sing?

07:12.000 --> 07:15.000
Millie asks Tom.

07:15.000 --> 07:17.000
He laughs.

07:17.000 --> 07:19.000
Let's see.

07:19.000 --> 07:21.000
He opens the door.

07:21.000 --> 07:24.000
No, Millie says.

07:24.000 --> 07:26.000
There's a full moon.

07:26.000 --> 07:30.000
We can't go out.

07:30.000 --> 07:37.000
You can stay here, but I want to see who's singing at midnight.

07:37.000 --> 07:44.000
Tom opens the door and they run into the corridor.

07:44.000 --> 07:50.000
Someone is singing in the music room, says Millie.

07:50.000 --> 07:54.000
You're right, says Tom.

07:54.000 --> 08:01.000
It's a man and he's singing a song about the sea.

08:01.000 --> 08:05.000
It's beautiful, says Millie.

08:05.000 --> 08:09.000
Is it Uncle Henry?

08:09.000 --> 08:12.000
Tom isn't listening.

08:12.000 --> 08:17.000
He opens the door of the music room and goes in.

08:17.000 --> 08:21.000
Don't, Tom, says Millie.

08:21.000 --> 08:27.000
We can't go into the music room.

08:27.000 --> 08:35.000
The music room is very big and Millie is afraid.

08:35.000 --> 08:41.000
We haven't got much time before Uncle Henry hears us.

08:41.000 --> 08:43.000
She says.

08:43.000 --> 08:49.000
Tom puts the light on and the singing stops.

08:49.000 --> 08:56.000
In the music room there's a piano and there are lots of pictures on the wall.

08:56.000 --> 08:59.000
But Uncle Henry isn't there.

08:59.000 --> 09:03.000
Millie wants to go.

09:03.000 --> 09:09.000
On one wall there is a very big picture of a ship.

09:09.000 --> 09:17.000
Millie and Tom look at the picture and they can see that the sea is moving.

09:17.000 --> 09:21.000
They can hear the water.

09:21.000 --> 09:25.000
There is a man standing on the ship.

09:25.000 --> 09:30.000
He has got long black hair and a black hat.

09:30.000 --> 09:34.000
He is singing a song about the sea.

09:34.000 --> 09:38.000
He's a pirate.

09:38.000 --> 09:43.000
Tom and Millie are afraid but they can't move.

09:43.000 --> 09:46.000
The pirate looks at them.

09:46.000 --> 09:50.000
He stops singing and he smiles.

09:50.000 --> 09:57.000
Suddenly he comes out of the picture and into the music room.

09:57.000 --> 09:59.000
Help!

09:59.000 --> 10:02.000
Shouts Millie.

10:02.000 --> 10:06.000
Millie looks at the handsome pirate.

10:06.000 --> 10:14.000
He has a big hat and he is very white.

10:14.000 --> 10:18.000
He's a ghost.

10:18.000 --> 10:22.000
She says in a quiet voice to Tom.

10:22.000 --> 10:27.000
Tom, let's go.

10:27.000 --> 10:31.000
Tom doesn't answer.

10:31.000 --> 10:37.000
The pirate is near the door so they can't go.

10:37.000 --> 10:43.000
Who's in my music room?

10:43.000 --> 10:45.000
The pirate shouts,

10:45.000 --> 10:50.000
This is my room.

10:50.000 --> 10:54.000
You're right, says Tom.

10:54.000 --> 11:01.000
This is your music room and we're going to bed.

11:01.000 --> 11:05.000
The pirate shakes his head.

11:05.000 --> 11:09.000
Oh no, you're not.

11:09.000 --> 11:12.000
Sit down.

11:12.000 --> 11:20.000
I'm going to tell you my story.

11:20.000 --> 11:29.000
My name is William Bones but everyone calls me Billy.

11:29.000 --> 11:32.000
Says the pirate.

11:32.000 --> 11:37.000
The year is 1793.

11:37.000 --> 11:47.000
My men and I sail the seven seas in my ship, the pearl.

11:47.000 --> 11:57.000
We fight pirate ships and we sing songs about the sea.

11:57.000 --> 12:07.000
We are very happy because we have lots of treasure.

12:07.000 --> 12:21.000
Then one day I help an old woman and she paints a picture of my ship.

12:21.000 --> 12:27.000
This picture's magic, she tells me.

12:27.000 --> 12:35.000
Before you die, put it in a house near the sea.

12:35.000 --> 12:47.000
When you die and the moon is full, your ghost can sail your ship for one night.

12:47.000 --> 12:54.000
Then the old woman looks at me and she says,

12:54.000 --> 13:07.000
Pirate Billy Bones, remember that the picture must be near the sea.

13:07.000 --> 13:12.000
Now it's 1850.

13:12.000 --> 13:14.000
Billy says,

13:14.000 --> 13:23.000
When I'm old, I die in my house by the sea.

13:23.000 --> 13:27.000
The old woman is right.

13:27.000 --> 13:37.000
When the moon is full, my ghost can sail my ship for one night.

13:37.000 --> 13:49.000
But then, in 1910, someone brings the picture here to manor all.

13:49.000 --> 13:51.000
The pirate says,

13:51.000 --> 14:02.000
This house isn't near the sea, so I can't sail my ship.

14:02.000 --> 14:09.000
When the moon is full, I sing songs about the sea.

14:09.000 --> 14:14.000
And the people in the house are afraid.

14:14.000 --> 14:18.000
They are afraid of the ghost.

14:18.000 --> 14:27.000
They put my picture in the music room and lock the door.

14:27.000 --> 14:33.000
Suddenly, the door of the music room opens.

14:33.000 --> 14:36.000
Uncle Henry stands there.

14:36.000 --> 14:43.000
He looks at Billy Bones and then at Tom and Millie.

14:43.000 --> 14:46.000
His face is white.

14:46.000 --> 14:51.000
Oh dear, he says,

14:51.000 --> 14:57.000
Now you know about the mystery.

14:57.000 --> 15:06.000
Now, I must tell you my story, says Uncle Henry.

15:06.000 --> 15:12.000
The year is 1976.

15:12.000 --> 15:17.000
I buy this house from an old man.

15:17.000 --> 15:24.000
He tells me about the picture and the ghost in the music room.

15:24.000 --> 15:31.000
I'm afraid of ghosts and I don't go into the music room.

15:31.000 --> 15:34.000
I lock the door.

15:34.000 --> 15:39.000
Every month, when there is a full moon,

15:39.000 --> 15:47.000
I hear a pirate singing songs about the sea, says Uncle Henry.

15:47.000 --> 15:51.000
I know that he is unhappy,

15:51.000 --> 15:56.000
and I know that he wants to go back to the sea.

15:56.000 --> 16:02.000
But I'm afraid, and I can't help him.

16:02.000 --> 16:06.000
I know, says Tom.

16:06.000 --> 16:14.000
Our new house is in a beautiful place near the sea, he says.

16:14.000 --> 16:23.000
From my bedroom, I can hear the sea gulls and the waves come with us.

16:23.000 --> 16:31.000
We can put your picture in the breakfast room where you can see the sea.

16:31.000 --> 16:35.000
Uncle Henry begins to smile.

16:35.000 --> 16:43.000
How wonderful, says Billy Bones.

16:43.000 --> 16:52.000
I'm happy that you want to go with Tom and Millie, says Uncle Henry.

16:52.000 --> 16:59.000
Please sit down, Billy Bones, and listen.

16:59.000 --> 17:03.000
Everyone sits at the kitchen table.

17:03.000 --> 17:09.000
You can go, but you must be quiet.

17:09.000 --> 17:16.000
You must sing quietly in their new house.

17:16.000 --> 17:21.000
All right, says Billy Bones.

17:21.000 --> 17:27.000
Are you afraid of ghosts now, Henry?

17:27.000 --> 17:29.000
Henry smiles.

17:29.000 --> 17:35.000
No, I'm not Billy.

17:35.000 --> 17:38.000
Mum's here, says Millie.

17:38.000 --> 17:41.000
They run out of the house.

17:41.000 --> 17:49.000
Mum, we have something from Uncle Henry, says Millie.

17:49.000 --> 17:54.000
It's for the new house.

17:54.000 --> 18:03.000
Mum looks at the picture, a ship, and a handsome pirate.

18:03.000 --> 18:08.000
How lovely, says Mum.

18:08.000 --> 18:14.000
Tom and Millie say goodbye to Uncle Henry.

18:14.000 --> 18:19.000
They take the picture to their new house by the sea.

18:19.000 --> 18:27.000
Pirate Billy Bones stands on his ship and he looks at his new home.

18:27.000 --> 18:35.000
He can hear seagulls and he quietly sings a song about the sea.

18:35.000 --> 18:44.000
One day, when there is a full moon, his ship disappears.

